						               													<description>The Sorts-Bocks are a set of 3 coasters. They represent 3 new special events.&amp;#10;During game set up, place the Sorts-Bocks next to each other on the table. Use as many as you want.&amp;#10;The gameplay remains unchanged with the exeptions of the following rule:&amp;#10;When a tower is distroyed and placed on the box, its owner check if this action starts a new floor. If it does not, nothing happens. But if it does, before activating the caracter power, the player can choose one or more of the available Sorts-Block and put it/them in play.&amp;#10;The 3 coasters are:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;. The pit: cancel the throw &amp;#10;. The wall: forces a player to place it vertically between two of his towers&amp;#10;. The bridge: forces a player to place it horizontally between two of his towers&amp;#10;&amp;#10;French edition found in Plato Magazine 118&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
